                  <summary>A list of 4 <foreign>biruda</foreign>s on a capital stone found
							lying around the Shore temple.</summary>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <p>This is a biscript inscription. The honorific <foreign>śrī</foreign>
								is written in Siddhamātṛkā, while the rest of the inscription is in
								Grantha. The double <foreign>daṇḍa</foreign> is of the type where
								both <foreign>daṇḍa</foreign>s are joined.</p>
                  </handDesc>
               </physDesc>
